The police in Zamfara State have arrested 11 suspected bandits and recovered several arms from them. The Commissioner of Police, Kenneth Embrimson, said 11 locally made revolvers and Brownie pistols as well as 20 locally made guns were also recovered from suspected criminals. He said those arrested would be charged to court after investigation. Embrimson added that they also arrested 10 suspected criminals known as ‘Sara Suka’ terrorizing Gusau metropolis and two suspected kidnappers who sent threat letters to villages. He said the effort would be sustained in all parts of the state and urged members of the public to continue to collaborate with the command’s information network to enable them arrest crime in the state.